{"sequence":35,"timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:03:17.313431254Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-f924f41e","body":"Fix the implementer source-attribution regression in backend diagnostics. `src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs:427-435` now injects a compiled-default `workflow.implementer_backend` selection (`codex`) even when the user never set that key, and `src/contexts/agent_execution/diagnostics.rs:1482-1497` already treats that role as an explicit override for `backend check`/`probe`. But `src/contexts/agent_execution/diagnostics.rs:1526-1552` still collapses any default-sourced `workflow.implementer_backend` entry to `default_backend (...)`. In a fresh workspace, `backend show-effective --json` therefore reports the implementer as `codex/gpt-5.4-high` with `override_source = \"default_backend (default)\"`, even though changing `default_backend` no longer changes that role. Update `show-effective` to attribute the implementer to `workflow.implementer_backend` (or another explicit implementer-default label) whenever the role is resolved via the compiled implementer default, and add a regression test in `tests/unit/backend_diagnostics_test.rs`.","dedup_key":"969eb9430e4352689059c8e141a3b0c94a22db8197154707cf1a951425f695d6","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260412172012","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
