{"sequence":71,"timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:47:42.285633329Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-e6fe4b51","body":"Restore backward compatibility for the stable `backend show-effective` / `backend probe` contracts. `src/contexts/agent_execution/diagnostics.rs:76-109,785-792,830-835,1712-1765` removes the stable `role == \"final_reviewer\"` entry, replaces it with `final_review_panel.reviewer[i]`, and rejects `--role final_reviewer`. This bead only changes backend defaults, so existing consumers that key off the documented stable DTO or probe that role will now break. Keep a compatibility `final_reviewer` row/probe path (or version the DTO/CLI) and add the per-member reviewer rows as an additive change instead of a replacement.","dedup_key":"c2a139053c7a078e290bac738d92cedd5a8e10ddf72458a6b599f9f1ccdeb802","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260412172012","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":72,"timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:47:42.294645949Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-0a3c4ba5","body":"Fix `backend show-effective` model-source attribution for the new compiled Codex defaults. `src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs:1542-1546` now supplies the implementer and final-review defaults through `backends.codex.role_models.{implementer,final_reviewer}`, but `src/contexts/agent_execution/diagnostics.rs:1572-1630,1712-1745` suppresses role-model entries when their source is `Default` and falls back to the generic `\"default\"` label. On a fresh workspace that makes `implementer` (`gpt-5.4-high`) and `final_review_panel.reviewer[0]` (`gpt-5.4-xhigh`) report `model_source: \"default\"`, which points operators at the wrong control point. Return a role-model-specific default source string when the resolved model comes from a compiled `backends.<family>.role_models.<role>` default.","dedup_key":"8e2c7246397fea9370a80711fd7a5767fb9de5ec587d62a5a616ae3350bcaa84","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260412172012","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":73,"timestamp":"2026-04-12T18:47:42.303575052Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-0b4daea6","body":"Unify the legacy `BackendResolver` path with the new implementer default. `src/shared/domain.rs:252-256` changes the implementer default target to `codex/gpt-5.4-high`, but `src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs:43-92` still resets models with `ModelSpec::default_for_backend()` whenever a backend family changes. A simple `BackendResolver::resolve(Implementer, None, project=codex, workspace=claude)` now resolves to `codex/gpt-5.4`, silently dropping the required `-high` suffix. Any caller that still uses `BackendResolver` instead of `BackendPolicyService` can therefore see a different implementer default than the main workflow engine. Either teach `apply_selection` about role-specific defaults or route those callers through `BackendPolicyService`.","dedup_key":"45f237fdc68c7e497f2f6c610cb5f0e3f64c9f0399045269e364aaa75c77a629","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260412172012","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
