{"sequence":108,"timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:31:50.822760512Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-6-0736c40d","body":"Preserve `default_model` overrides for the new Codex defaults. `default_backend_runtime_settings()` now hardcodes `backends.codex.role_models.implementer = gpt-5.4-high` and `backends.codex.role_models.final_reviewer = gpt-5.4-xhigh` ([src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs:1542-1547]), `EffectiveConfig::load` makes the implementer backend selection explicit by default ([src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs:427-435]), and `target_for_family()` always prefers `role_models` over `base_backend.model/default_model` ([src/contexts/agent_execution/policy.rs:327-340]). As a result, a workspace/project override like `default_backend = \"codex\"` plus `default_model = \"override-model\"` no longer changes the implementer or first final-review reviewer: `backend probe --role implementer` / `final_reviewer` still resolve to `gpt-5.4-high` / `gpt-5.4-xhigh`. That regresses the existing workspace/project override path the bead explicitly says must keep working.","dedup_key":"2cc0f5ac30fbf5e377a771d3d9bf1574d7a9a90cc06792f10bd1328c5564b246","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260412172012","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
